<title>USA: TABLE-Ashanti Goldfields Q2 profit falls.</title>
<headline>TABLE-Ashanti Goldfields Q2 profit falls.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>3 months to   3 months to  6 months to  6 months to</p>
<p>	     30 June 1997 30 June 1996 30 June 1997 30 June 1996</p>
<p>		     US$m	   US$m	   US$m	   US$m</p>
<p>    Notes   (unaudited)  (unaudited)  (unaudited)  (unaudited)</p>
<p>Operating costs  (85.0)	 (85.1)	(169.6)    (150.9)</p>
<p>Total costs     (113.2)	(105.2)	(221.8)	(195.1)</p>
<p>Operating profit   15.1	   17.4	   38.8	   46.6</p>
<p>Share of earnings of</p>
<p>associated undertakings -	  0.7		-	    1.4</p>
<p>Profit for the financial</p>
<p>    period	     7.7	   13.4	   22.8	  38.6</p>
<p>Retained (loss)/profit</p>
<p>for the period     (5.9)	   13.4	    9.2	  26.6</p>
<p>Earnings per share (US$)  0.07   0.15	   0.21	  0.43</p>
<p>The company said it took an exceptional charge against second quarter earnings for the cost of a redundancy program.</p>
<p>The charge reduced the second quarter earnings to a net of $7.7 from the underlying level of $10.2 million.</p>
<p>Full name is Ashanti Goldfields Co Ltd.</p>
